.TH LIME-LSP 1 "June 2026" "Lime 0.12.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
lime-lsp \- Language Server Protocol server for Lime grammar files
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B lime-lsp
.RI [ options ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B lime-lsp
is a Language Server Protocol (LSP) server for
.B .lime
grammar files.
It speaks LSP 3.17 (subset) over standard input/output framed with
HTTP-style
.B Content-Length
headers.
The server is a separate binary from the
.BR lime (1)
parser generator: for live diagnostics it
.BR fork (2)/ exec (3)s
.B lime -L
on a temporary copy of the open document; for navigation features
(go-to-definition, hover, document outline) it runs an
in-process tokenizer.
.PP
.B lime-lsp
takes no positional arguments and reads / writes JSON-RPC 2.0
on stdio only.
There is no daemon mode and no socket transport; editor
integrations spawn the server as a child process per workspace.
.PP
v0.5.0 ships LSP "Phase 1": single-document scope, full-text
sync, diagnostics, definition, hover, document symbol.
v0.5.7 adds completion, references, rename (with prepareRename),
and semantic tokens \(em the four capabilities the v0.5.0 man
page explicitly listed as deferred.  See
.B docs/LSP.md
for the implementation guide and
.B editors/lime-lsp-config.md
for editor wire-up recipes (eglot, lsp-mode, Neovim
.BR lspconfig ,
VS Code).
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BI \-\-lime " path"
Path to the
.BR lime (1)
binary used for diagnostics.
Overrides
.B $LIME_BIN
and the
.B PATH
search.
.TP
.B \-\-version
Print the LSP server version (matches
.BR LIME_VERSION_STRING )
and exit.
.SH "ADVERTISED CAPABILITIES"
The
.B ServerCapabilities
object returned at
.B initialize
time is the authoritative list of supported features:
.PP
.RS
.EX
{
  "textDocumentSync": { "openClose": true, "change": 1, "save": true },
  "definitionProvider":     true,
  "hoverProvider":          true,
  "documentSymbolProvider": true,
  "referencesProvider":     true,
  "completionProvider":     { "triggerCharacters": ["%", " ", "."] },
  "renameProvider":         { "prepareProvider": true },
  "semanticTokensProvider": {
    "legend": {
      "tokenTypes":     ["keyword", "namespace", "class", "variable",
                         "function", "string", "number", "comment",
                         "operator", "type", "macro", "label"],
      "tokenModifiers": ["definition", "deprecated"]
    },
    "full": true
  }
}
.EE
.RE
.PP
.B "change: 1"
is
.B TextDocumentSyncKind.Full
-- the client sends the full buffer text on every
.BR didChange ;
incremental sync is deferred.
.PP
Per-method status:
.TP
.B initialize / initialized / shutdown / exit
Standard lifecycle.  The server returns
.B serverInfo.version
populated from
.BR LIME_VERSION_STRING .
.TP
.B textDocument/didOpen, didChange, didSave, didClose
Maintain the per-document buffer state and push diagnostics on
each event;
.B didClose
publishes an empty diagnostic array to clear stale markers.
.TP
.B textDocument/publishDiagnostics
Server-to-client notification.
For each open document, parsed
.B lime -L
output (lint and parser-stage messages) becomes an LSP
.BR Diagnostic ;
severity maps:
.B error
\(rA 1,
.B warning
\(rA 2,
.B note / info
\(rA 3,
.B hint
\(rA 4.
.TP
.B textDocument/definition
Jump from a non-terminal RHS reference to its LHS-defining rule,
or from a terminal use to the
.B %token
declaration site.
.TP
.B textDocument/hover
Return either a one-line directive description (covering
.BR %name ,
.BR %token ,
.BR %type ,
.BR %extra_argument ,
.BR %extends ,
.BR %dialect ,
.BR %embed ,
.BR %locations ,
and the rest of the directive surface), or a symbol summary
(kind, declaring line, usage count).
.TP
.B textDocument/documentSymbol
Flat outline of every directive, terminal, and non-terminal in
the document, in declaration order with kinds
.B Key
(directive),
.B Constant
(terminal),
.B Function
(non-terminal).
.TP
.B textDocument/completion
Context-aware suggestions.  Three modes:
directive context (cursor on or just after a leading
.B %
at the start of a line) emits the full curated list of
recognized directives;
RHS context (cursor inside a rule, after
.B ::=
before the terminating
.BR . )
emits every terminal + non-terminal known to the open document,
prefix-filtered;
token-list context (cursor inside a
.B %token
/
.B %left
/
.B %right
/
.B %nonassoc
/
.B %type
/
.B %fallback
/
.B %wildcard
statement) emits terminals.
Trigger characters
.RB ( % ,
space,
.BR . )
are advertised in
.BR completionProvider.triggerCharacters .
Directive list is hard-coded in
.B src/lsp/lsp_navigation.c::kDirectiveDocs ,
shared with the hover handler; v0.5.8+ may parse it from
.BR lime_grammar (5).
.TP
.B textDocument/references
Resolves the symbol under the cursor and returns one
.B Location
per occurrence (definition + every reference site).
The
.B context.includeDeclaration
flag toggles inclusion of definition sites; pass
.B false
to get use-only references.  Cross-document propagation across
.B %extends
/
.B %import
is a v0.5.8+ follow-up; v0.5.7 is single-document.
.TP
.B textDocument/prepareRename
Validates that the cursor sits on a renameable symbol (a
terminal or non-terminal whose definition is in the open
document).  Returns
.B { range, placeholder }
on success and
.B null
on a non-renameable position (directive, comment, whitespace,
unknown identifier).  The editor surfaces null as a non-modal
status message, not an error popup, per LSP convention.
.TP
.B textDocument/rename
Returns a
.B WorkspaceEdit
.RB ( changes :
URI \(rA TextEdit[]) replacing every occurrence with
.BR newName .
Validation:
.B newName
must match
.BR [A-Za-z_][A-Za-z0-9_]* ;
must not collide with an existing symbol of a different kind;
must not match an existing
.BR % -directive
name.
A validation failure returns JSON-RPC error
.B \-32602
so the editor surfaces the reason verbatim.
Multi-file rename across
.B %extends
is a v0.5.8+ follow-up.
.TP
.B textDocument/semanticTokens/full
Returns a SemanticTokens object
.RB ( { data:
.RI [ deltaLine ,
.IR deltaStart ,
.IR length ,
.IR tokenType ,
.IR tokenMods ]*
.BR } )
encoding every classified lexical token in the document, in
source order, using the legend advertised at
.BR initialize .
Legend (12 token types):
.B keyword
(directive),
.B namespace
.RB ( %dialect
/
.B %extends
/
.B %import
argument),
.B class
(terminal),
.B variable
(non-terminal),
.B function
(reserved),
.B string
.RB ( "..."
/
.BR '...' ),
.B number
(decimal literal),
.B comment
(block + line),
.B operator
.RB ( ::=
/
.B |
/
.B .
/
.B ,
/
.B ;
/
.B (
/
.B )
/
.B [
/
.B ]
/
.B {
/
.BR } ),
.B type ,
.B macro ,
.B label
(reserved for v0.5.8+).
Modifiers
.RB ( definition ,
.BR deprecated )
are reserved; v0.5.7 always emits zero.
.PP
The following methods are advertised as
.B unsupported
and are intentionally deferred:
.B textDocument/codeAction ,
.B workspace/symbol .
.B codeAction
pairs with the linter's auto-fix surface, which has not yet
been wired.
.SH "ENVIRONMENT"
.TP
.B LIME_BIN
Path to the
.B lime
binary used for diagnostics.
Searched in this order:
.B \-\-lime
argument,
.BR LIME_BIN ,
literal
.B lime
on
.BR PATH .
.TP
.B TMPDIR
Used for the temporary file that holds the open document while
.B lime -L
runs against it.
Falls back to
.B /tmp
when unset.
.SH "EXIT STATUS"
.TP
.B 0
Clean shutdown via the LSP
.B shutdown
\(rA
.B exit
sequence.
.TP
.B 1
LSP protocol violation, malformed JSON-RPC frame, or fatal I/O
error on stdio.
.TP
.B 2
Argument-parsing failure.
.SH "PROCESS MODEL"
.RS
.EX
editor  <-- JSON-RPC 2.0 over stdio -->  lime-lsp
                                            |
                                            +--> fork+exec  lime -L /tmp/<doc>.lime
                                            |    (per didOpen / didChange /
                                            |     didSave; output piped back
                                            |     and parsed line-by-line)
                                            |
                                            +--> in-process tokenizer
                                                 (definition, hover,
                                                  documentSymbol; ~250 LOC)
.EE
.RE
.PP
The LSP target is intentionally decoupled from the Lime parser
runtime: it does
.I not
link
.B lime_parser_lib
and does
.I not
include any header that would force a recompile when the
parser internals change.  Every byte the LSP ships lives in
.BR src/lsp/ .
.SH "WIRE FORMAT"
JSON-RPC 2.0 framed with HTTP-style headers:
.PP
.RS
.EX
Content-Length: <N>\\r\\n
\\r\\n
<N bytes of UTF-8 JSON>
.EE
.RE
.PP
The bundled JSON parser (\fBsrc/lsp/lsp_json.[ch]\fP) is
hand-rolled in ~600 lines and handles UTF-16 surrogate pairs
in
.B \\uXXXX
escapes; no external JSON dependency is linked.
.SH "LIMITATIONS"
.IP \(bu 2
Single document at a time.  Definition / hover / outline /
references / rename do not cross
.B %extends
or
.B %import
file boundaries; v0.5.8+ wires the cross-document grammar
model.
.IP \(bu 2
Full-text sync only (no incremental).
.IP \(bu 2
No code actions or workspace symbol search.
.IP \(bu 2
POSIX-only.  The diagnostics path requires
.BR fork (2),
.BR execvp (3),
and
.BR pipe (2).
On Windows, run the server inside WSL.  A native Win32
implementation is future work.
